reviews_data.review_text: I love this place so much! Coffee and food is amazing. The staff is so Sweet, caring and always greet you with the biggest smile on their face. Best local coffee place around!

Definitely not a good experience at this place. Ordered a coffee that was cold. They remade it, and the coffee was weak. The breakfast burrito was overheated and chewy. The muffing was old and stale. $28 later, not a very great experience for a place that can't do drip coffee right. I am sorry, guys, but that's just the basics.

Giving the place a 1 star because I didn’t actually get to grab coffee during business hours. I arrived to find a sign on the door stating they were closing early due to cleaning needs. Totally understandable, however, being a visitor to the area, how would I know where else to grab coffee from here! I tried to ask the folks inside for help but they ignored me after making eye contact.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Alyssa, I’m so sorry you weren’t able to grab a coffee yesterday! Our espresso machine was malfunctioning yesterday…the day before our one year anniversary party! It was a little stressful to say the least, but we managed to get a technician to come at 3pm which we posted on the door. That may have been who you saw inside. I’d ask you to reconsider a one star review because it really hurts our business. Hope to see you again now that our espresso machine is working!

reviews_data.review_text: Loved the vibe and the staff was super kind and friendly! The coffee was extremely bitter and sour. It was reminiscent of old hotel coffee and unfortunately, I couldn’t finish it, but based on other reviews I would definitely be willing to give it another try in the near future!
This place is just ok.
love the coffee sizes are a bit small but great coffee

This coffee shop is a standout: creative, unique, and anything but ordinary. If you’re looking to try something unforgettable, order the Rare Air. The flavor profile is next-level and truly one of the best I’ve ever had. The whole experience was thoroughly enjoyable, and while the prices are a bit on the higher side, it’s absolutely worth it. Not your average coffee shop by any means… I’ll definitely be coming back.
Cute little coffee shop. Coffee was good. Breakfast burrito was just ok.
Loved their unique drink options!
Ready good coffee, although the place seemed a little chaotic, looks like they are not fully operational yet.

First timer. I love it. Used it was a pitstop for a multi-mile walk. Kid friendly for sure! Its great weather permitting,  but whole there are a few spots inside, if you're planning to sit at your leisure,  it will be outdoors mostly.  Workers are super nice and prices are comparable to others. Like it!
Fantastic coffee, bites, and service. Reasonable prices also. We can’t wait to return!

Nice spot to grab a coffee or matcha during the week. The outdoor tables are a great touch, and they bring your order right to you. Overall, I’d definitely recommend this place to meet up with friends and enjoy a nice time.

Lately lattes are not consistent with the sweetener. Mostly too sweet but inconsistent based on who is making the lattes. The food is great. I hope all baristas will follow the same process going forward.

Such a cute find in Charlotte. We were nearby at a hotel and this was recommended for their matcha. Matcha didn’t disappoint one bit and the coffee options were very creative and delicious. Bit of a wait in line to order but it’s clear why they’re popular.
This is my go to coffee/ matcha place. Always so quick with the drinks and the pastries are great. The cumulus drink is the best!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind review! So glad you enjoy the Cumulus. See you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: The burrito is one of the best I’ve had but the coffee wasn’t up to the mark (sweet and weak).
Incredibly hospitable and friendly environment. Love the warm atmosphere and the rare air latte is a win every time!
I got the cumulus matcha drink and YUM! So refreshing and the toasted coconut flavor paired perfectly with the matcha flavor. The staff were so kind!
Excellent coffee , great service and the music selection was a plus . Will be back for sure !
Nice, clean and aesthetic coffee shop, with a unique array of drinks and desserts. Once you grab a nice cold drink, be sure to walk down to Stream Park and relax in one of the hammocks!
I like matcha. I like coconut. I like sweet things. But unfortunately the Cumulus was just too milky. I didn’t taste the matcha at all not even at the end of it.

Excellent coffee and incredible service. Every detail—from the flavor of the brew (shoutout to the Cloudburst) to the warm, welcoming atmosphere—shows care and creativity. Fly Kid Fly is a place you’ll want to come back to. Highly recommend!

Coffee was atrocious First time around.
Second visit, it was incredible.
Wonderful, informative service. Very kind people.
I'm glad I came back, it was worth the try
reviews_data.owner_answer:

Could you connect with me at hello@flykidfly.com so I can find a way to make it up to you?  Thanks for your feedback.

-Madison Currie

reviews_data.review_text:
Update: This is now one of the best places in Charlotte with really delicious coffee. I’m glad the management reads reviews and works on improving the service.

A pleasant place with the best beans I've tried in Charlotte. Unfortunately, they don't hire top-tier baristas. The milk is overheated, almost brought to a boil, even though I didn't ask for it. The espresso isn't always well-prepared. Out of three visits to this café, only once was the coffee made perfectly. I guess it depends on which shift is working that day. It's a shame because it's a great spot with a lot of potential.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Aleksandr,

Sorry to hear you haven't had great coffee experiences at our shop - it's honestly really suprising and disappointing. We pride ourselves on the coffee education and training our baristas go through which seems to have let us down in your experience.  Can you shed any light as to when you came, and any specific feedback aside from milk temperature?  We hope to make it up to you on your next visit.  Ask for Madison, and I'll hook you up. 

Cheers!

Madison Currie (Co-Owner)

reviews_data.review_text: Staff was unpleasant, they don’t take cash(the American currency 🙄), coffee was not good

It's a really cute and convenient location, the service was quick and everyone was friendly. The drinks were disappointing though - the three of us visiting got different drinks and they all tasted mostly like the milk. I could barely taste the matcha in my matcha latte. We were surprised because it was pretty busy there, seemingly popular. I probably won't go here again :(

reviews_data.review_text: Great coffee shop! I went out of my comfort zone and tried their Rare Air latte on their signature menu and it did not disappoint! Unique but delicious flavor combo of ube, cherry, cinnamon and cardamom. I will definitely be back!

This place is great, however, Sunday it closes at 4 pm which makes no sense at all. All of the restaurants and shops around it are open at 4 pm and this is the only place that closes. Very disappointing.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Raphael,
Glad to hear you love our shop and wish it was open more.  Unfortunatley, since we are a coffee shop that focuses on drinks that have caffeine, our open hours do differ from the evening-focused restaurants around us.  We tried staying open later in our first few months, but the sales didn't justify staying open any later than 4pm.  A 3-star review is tough for simply disagreeing with our hours and would ask you to reconsider.  Trust me, if I could justify being open later, I definitely would!

Either way, appreciate your feedback!  All the best.

-Madison Currie

reviews_data.review_text: I keep coming back to Fly Kid Fly for their unique specialty matcha beverage, the Cumulus. The combination of toasted coconut, matcha, and blue spirulina are incredibly delightful and smooth to the taste. No doubt one of my top 3 matcha drinks in Charlotte. I’ve tried their breakfast as well and enjoyed it. Everything here seems clean and the service is always lovely.

Just went there today and coffee was phenomenal! The place was clean and the staff was warm and friendly. The service was smooth and streamlined. Can’t recommend enough. Heard they’re opening a Matthews location and very excited for that!

Fly Kid Fly delivers a delightful experience for coffee enthusiasts and pastry lovers alike. During our visit, we sampled the Vanilla Latte, the Cloud Burst, and the Apple Cider Loaf. Each drink was expertly crafted. The Vanilla Latte was beautifully balanced with a subtle sweetness, while the Cloud Burst offered a unique and refreshing twist. The Apple Cider Loaf was the highlight, with a perfect blend of warmth and spice, making it an exceptional pairing with the drinks.

The staff were welcoming and efficient, even during a busier time. However, seating can be quite limited indoors, and despite the presence of outdoor heaters, it was a bit too cold to comfortably enjoy the outdoor seating.

We will come back to try other drinks in the many more future seasons.
Fantastic coffee shop, superb coffee, friendly staff who are willing to serve and make sure you are satisfied!
Amazing coffee shop! Kid friendly. Delicious teas and coffee. The owners are wonderful!

This Coffee is the BEST!!! Matcha 🍵 coffee I have ever had. I had Matcha coffee from Starbucks in the past it taste horrible. I really wish I came here sooner. I also had the breakfast burrito the classic. It was pretty good very melty. I just wish it was a little bit bigger.
Fairly good coffee. It's not the best I've had but it's above average.

Have to be honest here. I was SO excited for this coffee shop and was extremely disappointed on my first and only trip. The coffee was not great, the price WAY too much and the service was awful. The 2 girls behind the counter were having their own little convo while another guy cleaning up had to come around and get the order. I was the only one in line. In this economy there’s other smaller local coffee spots.

I can’t explain it but the vibes are just always off here. It feels so sterile which I get it’s the look they are going for but it just doesn’t feel welcoming. Definitely more of an upscale coffee place. Which I typically can appreciate but this just feels… intense. The space itself is very small and when you walk in the counter is right there so two people on line at the same time can barely fit. Make sure you know what you want because from my experiences this isn’t the type of place that they will make small talk or give recommendations or welcome engagement. I’ve tried both the coffee options and the tea options. Decent coffee and I like the matcha but I always feel like both are watered down if I get iced. The breakfast burrito is decent but VERY greasy and heavy. Both times I’ve had it I feel like it is filled with more potatoes than eggs. The pastries are ok but nothing I would go out of my way for. I will say this is not a place to go with more than 2 people. While the outside can accommodate, the inside absolutely cannot. During the week most tables and filled with people working and it’s not always easy to find seating.

As far as our space goes, unfortunately we are doing the best we can with a small space to make it warm, inviting, and friendly.  We know our style isn't for everybody, but always a bummer to hear when guests don't find it welcoming.  Know that's certainly not our intention! Madison Currie

reviews_data.review_text: I don’t leave reviews often but stumbled across this place while in the Ballantyne area. The atmosphere is so unique and whimsical as soon as you get in. It has a modern feel but not in the uninviting stale way new coffee shops can feel. The colors make it so happy inside, and on top of the amazing atmosphere the Cumulus latte I got was one of the best lattes I’ve had in my life (LA and New York Included). I hope this shop has great success and selfishly please branch out to Raleigh!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks so much for this kind and thoughtful review Alexandra!  Hope to see you again sometime!

reviews_data.review_text:
My new favorite coffee in Ballantyne. The espresso has a rich nutty taste without the bitter burnt after taste we’ve been getting used to from other places. My favorite order has been the vanilla latte, both hot and iced. The vanilla also very simple, doesn’t take like a store bought syrup. The menu is to the point, the pastry/ baked goods are good, but the coffee is the star of the show. Ample seating outside for nice weather days, limited seating indoors but cute work stations. Parking is general Bowl parking, some street, some lots but all free. Vegan and vegetarian options

On the weekends there is a line out the door but don’t let that scare you I think the setup just limits ordering room inside.
I am a matcha snob, and let me tell you that the cumulus matcha is the best I’ve ever had. It’s insane. Perfectly sweet and complex. Bravo 👏🏼
I love breakfast burritos and coffee!

Amazing atmosphere, they chose the perfect setting. Not sure if it was intentional, but the matching uniforms with the colors of the shop add, and the overall aesthetic is top notch. The Cumulus Matcha is gorgeous, not the strongest flavor, but it’s so beautiful. Great service!

Fun little coffee shop. Very cool and modern vibes. The baristas are top-notch, always very friendly and really know how to make good coffee. The matcha and vanilla latte are our go-to orders, always smooth and flavorful, and our toddler enjoys the lil dreamer drink. The breakfast burritos are quite delicious as well. It can get pretty busy on the weekends and indoor seating is limited, but there is plenty outdoor seating with heaters. Definitely a must-visit!

I’m not a coffee person, but I am a matcha person—and I have to say, the Cumulus Matcha is one of my favorites! It’s not your typical matcha; it has a unique twist that makes it so good. I haven’t even tried their regular matcha yet because I keep coming back to this one. Definitely worth a try if you’re a matcha lover!

Cute shop! Quick service and a friendly person at the register. Coffee prepared well, tasted alright.

What I am most concerned about are the painted/coated blue frothing pitchers that are chipping??
Had a very good latte here. Didn’t get a pic, super creamy. This spot is super minimalist I like it.

Doing great work as a newer more family friendly option for Hex coffee. Love their creative drinks and the breakfast burrito is an instant hit. Easy light breakfast and a great weekend way to start the morning

Saw the good reviews and thought they might serve specialty coffee here, which I was excited about. They serve HEX coffee based in CLT and only serve one coffee for batch brew and one coffee for espresso. Disappointed with lack of coffee offerings. They also don't do single pourovers either. The Ethiopian filter I ordered was OK at best as I felt it was a bit bitter and would've appreciated a brighter/sweeter cup, especially with their EK43 they use. I think for a quick grab and go spot, most will be satisfied but not really a place for the enthusiast focused.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Andy,

Sorry to hear you didn't love your Single Origin Filter.  We did make the choice to brew on Curtis Brewers with custom UFO sprayheads (sorry to get nerdy here) because we felt it offered better control, consistency, and produced better tasting coffees than the variability of pour overs. Generally, our coffee's are SUPER dialed in to be bright, juicy, and sweet coffees. Maybe you caught us on an off day.  Hope we can make it up to you next time!  Ask for Madison - and I'll make sure we get you a S.O. Filter that is more memorable.  

Cheers! 

Madison Currie (Co-Owner)

reviews_data.review_text: the chai, vanilla latte and chocolate chip banana bread are so good!
Madison and crew are awesome. I didn't know what to try and they gave great recommendations. The cloud burst was my favorite for this trip. It was a real treat!
Loved their matcha and last flight home latte!!!

Fly Kid Fly serves amazing coffee!
Friendly staff and a great vibe make it the perfect spot for a quality cup. Highly recommend!

Wow! I enjoyed this much more than I thought. This is hands down THE BEST specialty coffee place I have found in Charlotte. They have so many unique drinks, and they have Ube! I highly recommend checking this place out conveniently located in Ballantyne’s new Bowl.

Keep in mind we spent $39.00.
My fiancé and I are on a cross-country road trip to home after the holidays. With pep in our step and hearts three sizes bigger than the grinch, we segued through the Bowl on a friend’s glowing recommendation for “FlykidFly.”Mind you, his recommendation falls short of only  Emeral Lagase in our minds.

Sunday proved to be busy, as in standing room only. No problem right? We’re in the south and friendliness is thicker than grits or your grandmas accent. However, as my fiancé was looking over the menu/flyer someone took it from her. I would’ve slapped him, but I hadn’t left my manners in the car and I’m still recovering from a fractured spine.

We would’ve liked to have more latte options than the two presidential candidates we all voted on, but mocha and vanilla were enough I guess so we got the vanilla lattes along with two  “Brekky burritos”  (bacon and Barbacoa).

We found a spot to squeeze into (sort of), and when my name was called I politely worked my way to get it. The menu thief decided to stand right there so I kindly asked him to let me through to grab the food. As I grabbed the coffee, I noticed it was an inch from the top on my latte, but I was already annoyed so I ignored it. As I tried to exit around our esteemed menu connoisseur and his two lady friends, he decided to ignore my presence and bump the coffee which almost went everywhere, but we managed a light spill instead.

At this point I was ready to leave, but praise be to baby Jesus we had smashing window seats- who could imagine leaving? Well, the “brekky” (read like a valley girl), tortillas had soggy-spot syndrome along with crispy-dog-bone sections and eggs as bland as a preacher’s sermon on Monday, with so little meat that the leftovers from Jesus feeding the 5,000 would’ve been better.

To summarize, the coffee was excellent, but the experience and food made it underwhelming.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Isaiah,

Honestly, bravo on this review.  As negative as it is, I couldn't help laughing at the creativity.  We always appreciate feedback of all sorts - especially if it makes us better at what we do.  Sorry to hear there was a menu thief on the prowl.  We do our best to monitor that, but sometimes guests have their own ideas and we can't really stop it. 
As far as the brekky burrito feedback, we've taken this to our chef and are working on alternative heating options to avoid soggy/hard sections and proper salting.  It's tough when you're working with TurboChef ovens to have every burrito perfect - but we try.

Glad your coffee was good! 

Anyways, all the best to you wherever you live. Hope we can make it up to you on your next visit to Charlotte. 

Cheers!

Madison Currie (Co-Owner)

Yanel is a gem and makes my day better each time I have visited while she is in the store. Mattie goes out of his way to ensure you are welcomed and acknowledged. The staff are so friendly and the coffee is amazing!

We got the cloudburst (hot) and it was AMAZING! Very unique and delicious...
We also had a cortado which was excellent.. we love Hex coffee so it was nice to have it at a new location...

honestly a bit of a let down- I will go back to try their actual coffee but they’re food is not great. their brekky burrito didn’t have any flavor. I plan on sticking to sunflour, summit and littl madeline’s

This is a brand new local spot right next to the Ballantyne bowl!!

Madison was super friendly and gave us wonderful recommendations. I ordered the Last Flight Home drink, but I did not notice a cardamom sugar frosting rim or much of a cardamom taste, so I would highly recommend not getting the coffee to go to benefit from the flavored rim and a tiny bit of sweetness. However, the espresso was smooth and perfectly extracted with a beautiful La Marzocco machine.

This place has limited indoor space and seating, so be prepared to sit outside and enjoy the views!

Best coffee and breakfast burrito in all of Charlotte and it is not even close. Madison and the entire staff are incredible. Every person working is always attentive, kind, personable, and can each make a wildly good latte. I would not go to any other coffee shop in the area, no matter what you get, you will not be disappointed. Proud to be a regular here!!

Fly Kid Fly is hands-down one of my favorite spots! Their coffee is absolutely incredible—smooth, rich, and perfectly brewed every time. The breakfast burritos are an absolute must-try—fresh, flavorful, and the perfect start to the day. The staff here are the nicest people you’ll meet; they’re always welcoming and seem to know just the right recommendation for whatever you’re craving. I also had the apple cider loaf recently, and it was so delicious—perfectly spiced and just the right amount of sweetness. Highly recommend stopping by!
Great place! Loved the coffee! Service was excellent and the owner even stopped and talked to us for a while. The barista even gave us a stick on tattoo for our 1 year old. Will be back!
Tastes amazing would definitely recommend 💯 i got the little dreamer and it tasted so goood ✨
Quick, friendly service. Coffee was ok. Simple bar style seating.

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely delicious!

Absolutely incredible coffee shop. Vibes. Coffee. Customer Service. Family-friendly. Food. Everything is incredible. Skip every coffee shop in NC and go directly here - you won’t be disappointed - in fact; you’ll actually tell all your friends. Then your friends will tell all their friends &  their friends will all ask, “who told you about this place!??” And the answer will be YOU. You’ll be the cool person who introduced all these people to the greatest coffee shop in NC.

We were spending the morning hours walking around the Bowl and taking the kids to the near by playground, so seeing that a new coffee shop opened up I was happy to try it out!
Upon walking in, I noticed the giant menu on the back wall which I did not care for. It is difficult to read with all the letters jumbled together and the environment just seemed really plain to me.
I do not drink coffee, but I love Chai tea lattes which is what I ordered. Immediately, after being handed my drink I take my first sip and was thrown back at 2 things: the temperature and the flavor.
I ordered a hot chai which is always steamed, but this was luke-warm at best. The chai flavor was extremely strong and tasted very watered down like it was made with water too and not just milk. I am really not one to complain so we walked out and I tried enjoying it as much as possible, but the thought of spending the money on something and I could not even enjoy it, I felt like I had to say something.
I went back inside to let them know and she was happy to remake it for me. Since it tasted water down, I asked if they use water or milk and she said they put almond milk in it! Again, I was taken back because I never even requested almond milk and thankfully I do not have a nut allergy! (There is no description on the menu so just beware!) As far as I know, a chai latte is made with whole milk which is what I was expecting and almond milk is usually only used upon request and is an upcharge.
After she remade it, it was hotter, but still wasn't very good and I wasn't going to make an issue of it again so I let it be.  It is so unfortunate because I love the idea of having a coffee shop in the bowl, I'm just not pleased with the experience I had and don't have a desire to go back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Kayla,
I'm very sorry to hear you didn't have a great experience at our shop! We care deeply about making every experience memorable, and it sounds like we failed to do that with your visit.  My sincerest apologies.  Regarding the chai, we do make it with whole milk as the standard, so we must have mis-heard your order to have used almond milk. I'm very sorry about that.  I'm glad we remade it for you - sorry it wasn't to your liking.  We do use a very high-quality chai that has some spice to it.  I understand that's not everyone's preference.  If there is anything else you like to drink at coffee shops, I"d love to make for you.  Ask for Madison next time you're in so we can take care of you! 

All the best,

Madison

reviews_data.review_text: GET THE BREAKFAST BURRITO. With the hot sauce side. Top notch. Good cold brew too. Would definitely come back

First time visiting this Saturday and ordered an iced Cortado. The Cortado was literally just half full and no where near the top of the cup. I also wish there were more flavor options such as different syrups. They only had two options wish is weird because what if a person doesn’t like or can’t have either option, wish was only vanilla and mocha. Not sure if I’d return.

Had a Cappuccino. While paper cup looked small it was filled to rim and tasted good.
Had an unfortunate mishap here. I went to add sugar and half&half laying on small table next to entrance door. The seating stool was placed so near to the coffee and sugar table that a teenage girl who was busy chatting with her friend with lot of hand movements and her back was facing me and sugar table.
She had no clue I was behind her adding sugar to my coffee.
I was already thinking that why this seating stool is placed so close to the sugar counter which anyone can easily strike their hand to any drinks laying on that counter. I was processing that thought and sure enough her hand struck the coffee cup, spilled on my white t-shirt and spilled on floor.
Staff was nice to replace the coffee with a new one.
Advice to the manager: please have your sugar milk counter next to water dispenser counter away from those stools where people are seating. Anyone can easily strike the drink cups accidentally if they are not aware of the counter.
Love this spot!!
Excellent lattes and amazing customer service! Please don’t change 💜
Everything from the coffee to the service is exceptional ! We love having them in our neighborhood

reviews_data.review_text: Great food options and the coffee was excellent!

Came for a breakfast burrito right when they opened and they didn’t have any. Pretty disappointing to plan my morning around going here and not get breakfast. Pretty good coffee and staff was very nice!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Mark,
I'm very sorry we were out of brekky burritos when you arrived today. Nothing worse than looking forward to something and being let down - fully undestand that. The truth is we have been shocked by the brekky burrito demand and simply sold out faster than we expected over the weekend.  Our offsite kitchen is trying to keep up, and should be good moving forward.  We were re-loaded this afternoon, and will be slinging burritos in the morning.  If you can, please stop by so I can treat you to one - just ask for Madison. It'll be worth it, I promise. 

All the best,

Madison

reviews_data.review_text:
Grabbed a coffee before Veg Fest. The Team was absolutely crushing it. Had a line but they were calm, collected and moved through it quickly. Had the Cumulus (matcha coconut) drink iced. It was excellent. I’ll be back for a burrito.

It’s mostly outdoor seating so plan accordingly. If the weather is nice or you’re grabbing on the go this should be your spot.

reviews_data.review_text:
Fly kid Fly is fantastic. Lovely Customer service , creative drinks, tasty filter coffee. Breakfast Burritos are so good!

Great addition to the Ballantyne Community.

Come to the shop ready to have fun. Because this shop is a good time!
Great coffee, friendly service and great location next to the parking lot.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind review! Glad you enjoyed your experience.

reviews_data.review_text: The baristas were super friendly, the coffee was great, and the aesthetic was unique! There is not much indoor seating but plenty of outdoor seating.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for coming by Madison! Glad you enjoyed your experience!

reviews_data.review_text:
Visited Fly Kid Fly for our first time and the inside of this coffee shop was nice and modern. The coffee shop is very small inside so there is limited seating inside so just be aware when you visit here.

The coffee wasn’t bad; however, my wife and I got our iced lattes and it was not filled up all the way which was disappointing especially for the price we paid. The coffee tasted good, but we felt like we got skimped on the serving. We understand they’re still learning so we hope it gets better soon.

We will return back, but will give it some time so they can work out their kinks.

My wife and I are excited for their Matthews location to open and hope it’s a larger coffee shop to be able to sit in and relax.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey there Andy,
I am genuinely so sorry that your drinks were not filled all the way.  I can assure you that was not intentional, but a misstep on a busy Saturday.  One of our core values as a company is to always be generous to our guests, so this is very disappointing to see.  We'd love to make it up to you next time you're in.  Please ask for Madison Currie, and I'll be sure to take care of you. 

All the best,

Madison Currie

reviews_data.review_text: Very tasty.
reviews_data.owner_answer: So glad you enjoyed!

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best coffee shops in all of NC. Coffee is dialed, and has everything for both the average coffee drinker and the specialty coffee lover. Hospitality was next level. Thank you for having a coffee shop that actually brings your order to your table! Old school service for the win. Breakfast burritos are unreal. The vibe is so fun and has such a cool/subtle nod to flights and airplanes. Love the kid specific drink too! A must visit, family friendly, specialty coffee shop.

reviews_data.review_text: Super cute spot!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!  Glad you enjoyed your experience!

reviews_data.review_text: My new favorite coffee shop. The Cloudburst was a great beverage and they nailed the Brekky Burrito. I also like that they bring your order to the table and you don't have to wait at the counter. I definitely plan to be back soon!

Got a hot mocha - very simple and flavor was as expected. Thought it was strange that no lid was given especially since this location is mostly outside seating. With it being a cooler, windy day, a lid would have helped keep coffee warmer. Food selection was average - standard pastries, nothing special.
Biggest things was the overall vibe was too modern feeling for my taste. Coffee shops should feel warm and inviting and I did not get this feeling with the aesthetics. People were friendly but overall vibe was not one where I would like to return to hang out, do a little work, etc. Wish you all well just not my preference in location.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Kat,
So sorry you didn't have a great experience with us! We keep our lids on the condiment station for people to add anything they need before lidding it. You should have been told where they are, so that's our fault! We do hope you come back so we can make it up to you sometime!  Just ask for Madison Currie. 

All the best! 

-Madison

reviews_data.review_text:
Fantastic new coffee shop bringing great third wave coffee to an area of Charlotte without it! It’s not often you get great third wave coffee paired with a fun, family friendly, + welcoming atmosphere.

Regular coffee bevs are top notch and the specialty drinks add a fun layer and unique twist to the coffee scene that isn’t present much in the Charlotte coffee scene. Burritos and salsa are fantastic.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Will! We are so stoked you enjoyed your time here.  Next time you're in, be sure to let us know so we can give you a high-five!

reviews_data.review_text: Many quality options to choose from, with reasonable prices. I went with the single-origin drip coffee and breakfast burrito which were solid. New go-to in the Ballantyne area.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Christopher!  So glad you enjoyed your experience!

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve been patiently waiting for this opening because Ballantyne was really lacking in coffee shop options, and it was so worth the wait. Impeccable vibes, delicious drinks, beautiful branding and so many fun details. My toddler was a big fan of his special blue milk steamer and the cute temporary tattoo. I will be back to try the breakfast burritos another time but we saw some coming out and they looked amazing too. My matcha and husband’s cold brew were both top notch. Will definitely be coming back often.

reviews_data.review_text: This coffee was so amazing! Jewel was excellent at explaining the menu and her customer service was ON POINT. The iced vanilla latte she recommended filled the cracks in my heart and the vegan banana bread, I will be back for more. Overall super cute shop! Great vibes

reviews_data.review_text: Love the coffee, the staff is very friendly, the breakfast burrito was really good!
reviews_data.owner_answer: So glad you enjoyed your visit Josh!  Thanks for taking the time to review!

reviews_data.review_text: This is an amazing coffee shop! So glad we stopped in! Pastries were yummy and homemade, service was top notch, both the energy and vibe were great and everyone was very welcoming. Management was on point and the area around the coffee shop was so nice. We really enjoyed the outside seating, although there was great seating inside as well. There was wonderful customer service from Kara who took our order. She was very helpful, intentional and took great care of us. Deanna made the best London fog that I’ve ever had and my friend had the vanilla iced latte and said it was wonderful! I also had the matcha since the tea was so good and it was equally amazing! We decided to split the orange cinnamon roll while there and take home the cookie sandwich to my husband and son and both were delicious. They also had breakfast burritos which looked really good, so I think I’ll try that next time. This is a place I can easily say I could spend hours at. Thank you so much for the hospitality that was shown and creating such a wonderful atmosphere and serving such yummy drinks and food. Nothing went unnoticed.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Wow, thank you so much for the kind and thoughtful review! So glad you enjoyed your visit. This means a ton, and will definitely be shared with the team. Please say hi next time you’re in! 

-Madison

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome new coffee shop. Great location, good selection of pastries and breakfast burritos. Welcoming atmosphere and great customer service. Deanna recommended and made a perfect glass of iced vanilla latte! 100% recommend!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the kind review Nikolay!  So glad you enjoyed your visit.  Deanna is the best.  Come see us again sometime!

reviews_data.review_text: I love this place so much! Coffee and food is amazing. The staff is so Sweet, caring and always greet you with the biggest smile on their face. Best local coffee place around!

Definitely not a good experience at this place. Ordered a coffee that was cold. They remade it, and the coffee was weak. The breakfast burrito was overheated and chewy. The muffing was old and stale. $28 later, not a very great experience for a place that can't do drip coffee right. I am sorry, guys, but that's just the basics.

Giving the place a 1 star because I didn’t actually get to grab coffee during business hours. I arrived to find a sign on the door stating they were closing early due to cleaning needs. Totally understandable, however, being a visitor to the area, how would I know where else to grab coffee from here! I tried to ask the folks inside for help but they ignored me after making eye contact.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Hey Alyssa, I’m so sorry you weren’t able to grab a coffee yesterday! Our espresso machine was malfunctioning yesterday…the day before our one year anniversary party! It was a little stressful to say the least, but we managed to get a technician to come at 3pm which we posted on the door. That may have been who you saw inside. I’d ask you to reconsider a one star review because it really hurts our business. Hope to see you again now that our espresso machine is working!

reviews_data.review_text: Loved the vibe and the staff was super kind and friendly! The coffee was extremely bitter and sour. It was reminiscent of old hotel coffee and unfortunately, I couldn’t finish it, but based on other reviews I would definitely be willing to give it another try in the near future!
This place is just ok.
love the coffee sizes are a bit small but great coffee

This coffee shop is a standout: creative, unique, and anything but ordinary. If you’re looking to try something unforgettable, order the Rare Air. The flavor profile is next-level and truly one of the best I’ve ever had. The whole experience was thoroughly enjoyable, and while the prices are a bit on the higher side, it’s absolutely worth it. Not your average coffee shop by any means… I’ll definitely be coming back.
Cute little coffee shop. Coffee was good. Breakfast burrito was just ok.
Loved their unique drink options!
Ready good coffee, although the place seemed a little chaotic, looks like they are not fully operational yet.

First timer. I love it. Used it was a pitstop for a multi-mile walk. Kid friendly for sure! Its great weather permitting,  but whole there are a few spots inside, if you're planning to sit at your leisure,  it will be outdoors mostly.  Workers are super nice and prices are comparable to others. Like it!
Fantastic coffee, bites, and service. Reasonable prices also. We can’t wait to return!

Nice spot to grab a coffee or matcha during the week. The outdoor tables are a great touch, and they bring your order right to you. Overall, I’d definitely recommend this place to meet up with friends and enjoy a nice time.

Lately lattes are not consistent with the sweetener. Mostly too sweet but inconsistent based on who is making the lattes. The food is great. I hope all baristas will follow the same process going forward.

Such a cute find in Charlotte. We were nearby at a hotel and this was recommended for their matcha. Matcha didn’t disappoint one bit and the coffee options were very creative and delicious. Bit of a wait in line to order but it’s clear why they’re popular.
This is my go to coffee/ matcha place. Always so quick with the drinks and the pastries are great. The cumulus drink is the best!

Excellent coffee , great service and the music selection was a plus . Will be back for sure !

reviews_data.review_text:
Update: This is now one of the best places in Charlotte with really delicious coffee. I’m glad the management reads reviews and works on improving the service.

A pleasant place with the best beans I've tried in Charlotte. Unfortunately, they don't hire top-tier baristas. The milk is overheated, almost brought to a boil, even though I didn't ask for it. The espresso isn't always well-prepared. Out of three visits to this café, only once was the coffee made perfectly. I guess it depends on which shift is working that day. This place is great, however, Sunday it closes at 4 pm which makes no sense at all. All of the restaurants and shops around it are open at 4 pm and this is the only place that closes. Very disappointing.

We tried staying open later in our first few months, but the sales didn't justify staying open any later than 4pm.  A 3-star review is tough for simply disagreeing with our hours and would ask you to reconsider.  Trust me, if I could justify being open later, I definitely would!

Either way, appreciate your feedback!  All the best.

reviews_data.review_text: I keep coming back to Fly Kid Fly for their unique specialty matcha beverage, the Cumulus. The combination of toasted coconut, matcha, and blue spirulina are incredibly delightful and smooth to the taste. No doubt one of my top 3 matcha drinks in Charlotte. I’ve tried their breakfast as well and enjoyed it. Everything here seems clean and the service is always lovely.

Just went there today and coffee was phenomenal! The place was clean and the staff was warm and friendly. The service was smooth and streamlined. Can’t recommend enough. Heard they’re opening a Matthews location and very excited for that!

Fly Kid Fly delivers a delightful experience for coffee enthusiasts and pastry lovers alike. During our visit, we sampled the Vanilla Latte, the Cloud Burst, and the Apple Cider Loaf. Each drink was expertly crafted. The Vanilla Latte was beautifully balanced with a subtle sweetness, while the Cloud Burst offered a unique and refreshing twist. The Apple Cider Loaf was the highlight, with a perfect blend of warmth and spice, making it an exceptional pairing with the drinks.

The staff were welcoming and efficient, even during a busier time. However, seating can be quite limited indoors, and despite the presence of outdoor heaters, it was a bit too cold to comfortably enjoy the outdoor seating.

We will come back to try other drinks in the many more future seasons.
Fantastic coffee shop, superb coffee, friendly staff who are willing to serve and make sure you are satisfied!
Amazing coffee shop! Kid friendly. Delicious teas and coffee. The owners are wonderful!

This Coffee is the BEST!!! Matcha 🍵 coffee I have ever had. I had Matcha coffee from Starbucks in the past it taste horrible. I really wish I came here sooner. I also had the breakfast burrito the classic. It was pretty good very melty. I just wish it was a little bit bigger.
Fairly good coffee. It's not the best I've had but it's above average.

Have to be honest here. I was SO excited for this coffee shop and was extremely disappointed on my first and only trip. The coffee was not great, the price WAY too much and the service was awful. The 2 girls behind the counter were having their own little convo while another guy cleaning up had to come around and get the order. I was the only one in line. In this economy there’s other smaller local coffee spots.

I can’t explain it but the vibes are just always off here. It feels so sterile which I get it’s the look they are going for but it just doesn’t feel welcoming. Definitely more of an upscale coffee place. Which I typically can appreciate but this just feels… intense. The space itself is very small and when you walk in the counter is right there so two people on line at the same time can barely fit. Make sure you know what you want because from my experiences this isn’t the type of place that they will make small talk or give recommendations or welcome engagement. I’ve tried both the coffee options and the tea options. Decent coffee and I like the matcha but I always feel like both are watered down if I get iced. The breakfast burrito is decent but VERY greasy and heavy. Both times I’ve had it I feel like it is filled with more potatoes than eggs. The pastries are ok but nothing I would go out of my way for. I will say this is not a place to go with more than 2 people. While the outside can accommodate, the inside absolutely cannot. During the week most tables and filled with people working and it’s not always easy to find seating.

reviews_data.review_text: I don’t leave reviews often but stumbled across this place while in the Ballantyne area. The atmosphere is so unique and whimsical as soon as you get in. It has a modern feel but not in the uninviting stale way new coffee shops can feel. The colors make it so happy inside, and on top of the amazing atmosphere the Cumulus latte I got was one of the best lattes I’ve had in my life (LA and New York Included). I hope this shop has great success and selfishly please branch out to Raleigh!

reviews_data.review_text:
My new favorite coffee in Ballantyne. The espresso has a rich nutty taste without the bitter burnt after taste we’ve been getting used to from other places. My favorite order has been the vanilla latte, both hot and iced. The vanilla also very simple, doesn’t take like a store bought syrup. The menu is to the point, the pastry/ baked goods are good, but the coffee is the star of the show. Ample seating outside for nice weather days, limited seating indoors but cute work stations. Parking is general Bowl parking, some street, some lots but all free. Vegan and vegetarian options

On the weekends there is a line out the door but don’t let that scare you I think the setup just limits ordering room inside.
I am a matcha snob, and let me tell you that the cumulus matcha is the best I’ve ever had. It’s insane. Perfectly sweet and complex. Bravo 👏🏼
I love breakfast burritos and coffee!

Amazing atmosphere, they chose the perfect setting. Not sure if it was intentional, but the matching uniforms with the colors of the shop add, and the overall aesthetic is top notch. The Cumulus Matcha is gorgeous, not the strongest flavor, but it’s so beautiful. Great service!

Fun little coffee shop. Very cool and modern vibes. The baristas are top-notch, always very friendly and really know how to make good coffee. The matcha and vanilla latte are our go-to orders, always smooth and flavorful, and our toddler enjoys the lil dreamer drink. The breakfast burritos are quite delicious as well. It can get pretty busy on the weekends and indoor seating is limited, but there is plenty outdoor seating with heaters. Definitely a must-visit!

I’m not a coffee person, but I am a matcha person—and I have to say, the Cumulus Matcha is one of my favorites! It’s not your typical matcha; it has a unique twist that makes it so good. I haven’t even tried their regular matcha yet because I keep coming back to this one. Definitely worth a try if you’re a matcha lover!

Cute shop! Quick service and a friendly person at the register. Coffee prepared well, tasted alright.

What I am most concerned about are the painted/coated blue frothing pitchers that are chipping??
Had a very good latte here. Didn’t get a pic, super creamy. This spot is super minimalist I like it.

Doing great work as a newer more family friendly option for Hex coffee. Love their creative drinks and the breakfast burrito is an instant hit. Easy light breakfast and a great weekend way to start the morning

Saw the good reviews and thought they might serve specialty coffee here, which I was excited about. They serve HEX coffee based in CLT and only serve one coffee for batch brew and one coffee for espresso. Disappointed with lack of coffee offerings. They also don't do single pourovers either. The Ethiopian filter I ordered was OK at best as I felt it was a bit bitter and would've appreciated a brighter/sweeter cup, especially with their EK43 they use. I think for a quick grab and go spot, most will be satisfied but not really a place for the enthusiast focused.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Andy,

Sorry to hear you didn't love your Single Origin Filter.  We did make the choice to brew on Curtis Brewers with custom UFO sprayheads (sorry to get nerdy here) because we felt it offered better control, consistency, and produced better tasting coffees than the variability of pour overs. Generally, our coffee's are SUPER dialed in to be bright, juicy, and sweet coffees. Maybe you caught us on an off day.  Hope we can make it up to you next time!  Ask for Madison - and I'll make sure we get you a S.O. Filter that is more memorable.  

Cheers! 

Madison Currie (Co-Owner)

reviews_data.review_text: the chai, vanilla latte and chocolate chip banana bread are so good!
Madison and crew are awesome. I didn't know what to try and they gave great recommendations. The cloud burst was my favorite for this trip. It was a real treat!
Loved their matcha and last flight home latte!!!

Fly Kid Fly serves amazing coffee!
Friendly staff and a great vibe make it the perfect spot for a quality cup. Highly recommend!

Wow! I enjoyed this much more than I thought. This is hands down THE BEST specialty coffee place I have found in Charlotte. They have so many unique drinks, and they have Ube! I highly recommend checking this place out conveniently located in Ballantyne’s new Bowl.

Keep in mind we spent $39.00.
My fiancé and I are on a cross-country road trip to home after the holidays. With pep in our step and hearts three sizes bigger than the grinch, we segued through the Bowl on a friend’s glowing recommendation for “FlykidFly.”Mind you, his recommendation falls short of only  Emeral Lagase in our minds.

Sunday proved to be busy, as in standing room only. No problem right? We’re in the south and friendliness is thicker than grits or your grandmas accent. However, as my fiancé was looking over the menu/flyer someone took it from her. I would’ve slapped him, but I hadn’t left my manners in the car and I’m still recovering from a fractured spine.

We would’ve liked to have more latte options than the two presidential candidates we all voted on, but mocha and vanilla were enough I guess so we got the vanilla lattes along with two  “Brekky burritos”  (bacon and Barbacoa).

We found a spot to squeeze into (sort of), and when my name was called I politely worked my way to get it. The menu thief decided to stand right there so I kindly asked him to let me through to grab the food. As I grabbed the coffee, I noticed it was an inch from the top on my latte, but I was already annoyed so I ignored it. As I tried to exit around our esteemed menu connoisseur and his two lady friends, he decided to ignore my presence and bump the coffee which almost went everywhere, but we managed a light spill instead.

At this point I was ready to leave, but praise be to baby Jesus we had smashing window seats- who could imagine leaving? Well, the “brekky” (read like a valley girl), tortillas had soggy-spot syndrome along with crispy-dog-bone sections and eggs as bland as a preacher’s sermon on Monday, with so little meat that the leftovers from Jesus feeding the 5,000 would’ve been better.

To summarize, the coffee was excellent, but the experience and food made it underwhelming.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Isaiah,

Honestly, bravo on this review.  As negative as it is, I couldn't help laughing at the creativity.  We always appreciate feedback of all sorts - especially if it makes us better at what we do.  Sorry to hear there was a menu thief on the prowl.  We do our best to monitor that, but sometimes guests have their own ideas and we can't really stop it. 
As far as the brekky burrito feedback, we've taken this to our chef and are working on alternative heating options to avoid soggy/hard sections and proper salting.  It's tough when you're working with TurboChef ovens to have every burrito perfect - but we try.

Glad your coffee was good! 

Anyways, all the best to you wherever you live. Hope we can make it up to you on your next visit to Charlotte. 

Cheers!

Madison Currie (Co-Owner)

reviews_data.review_text: Hands down the best coffee I have had in Charlotte. What makes this place special is the staff is better than the coffee. Yanel is a gem and makes my day better each time I have visited while she is in the store. Mattie goes out of his way to ensure you are welcomed and acknowledged. Everyone else in the store is always engaged and proving a great experience for the customer. Could not recommend a coffee shop more!

reviews_data.review_text: From a marketing perspective, the branding and aesthetic is perfect. It’s beautiful. The blue matcha drink was amazing! The staff were great. I did also try an almond vanilla ice latte and it was okay just a bit plainer than what I thought, just your typical latte but the other stuff on the menu is what makes this place stand out. Overall, would def come here again and again. 4.8/5 for me!
The design + the bakery + the coffee 🤝
The staff are so friendly and the coffee is amazing!

We got the cloudburst (hot) and it was AMAZING! Very unique and delicious...
We also had a cortado which was excellent.. we love Hex coffee so it was nice to have it at a new location...
We had a citrus cinnamon roll and while the flavor was good, it was pretty dry
Cool folks. Cool place. Hot coffee. Dope interior design.
Absolutely love this place! Very cute atmosphere, the staff is very cute and friendly. Madi the manager is great. The cumulus is phenomenal and the coffee is delicious!

honestly a bit of a let down- I will go back to try their actual coffee but they’re food is not great. their brekky burrito didn’t have any flavor. I plan on sticking to sunflour, summit and littl madeline’s

This is a brand new local spot right next to the Ballantyne bowl!!

Madison was super friendly and gave us wonderful recommendations. I ordered the Last Flight Home drink, but I did not notice a cardamom sugar frosting rim or much of a cardamom taste, so I would highly recommend not getting the coffee to go to benefit from the flavored rim and a tiny bit of sweetness. However, the espresso was smooth and perfectly extracted with a beautiful La Marzocco machine.

This place has limited indoor space and seating, so be prepared to sit outside and enjoy the views!

Best coffee and breakfast burrito in all of Charlotte and it is not even close. Madison and the entire staff are incredible. Every person working is always attentive, kind, personable, and can each make a wildly good latte. I would not go to any other coffee shop in the area, no matter what you get, you will not be disappointed. Proud to be a regular here!!

Fly Kid Fly is hands-down one of my favorite spots! Their coffee is absolutely incredible—smooth, rich, and perfectly brewed every time. The breakfast burritos are an absolute must-try—fresh, flavorful, and the perfect start to the day. The staff here are the nicest people you’ll meet; they’re always welcoming and seem to know just the right recommendation for whatever you’re craving. I also had the apple cider loaf recently, and it was so delicious—perfectly spiced and just the right amount of sweetness. Highly recommend stopping by!
Great place! Loved the coffee! Service was excellent and the owner even stopped and talked to us for a while. The barista even gave us a stick on tattoo for our 1 year old. Will be back!
Tastes amazing would definitely recommend 💯 i got the little dreamer and it tasted so goood ✨
Quick, friendly service. Coffee was ok. Simple bar style seating.

reviews_data.review_text: Absolutely delicious!

Absolutely incredible coffee shop. Vibes. Coffee. Customer Service. Family-friendly. Food. Everything is incredible. Skip every coffee shop in NC and go directly here - you won’t be disappointed - in fact; you’ll actually tell all your friends. Then your friends will tell all their friends &  their friends will all ask, “who told you about this place!??” And the answer will be YOU. You’ll be the cool person who introduced all these people to the greatest coffee shop in NC.

We were spending the morning hours walking around the Bowl and taking the kids to the near by playground, so seeing that a new coffee shop opened up I was happy to try it out!
Upon walking in, I noticed the giant menu on the back wall which I did not care for. It is difficult to read with all the letters jumbled together and the environment just seemed really plain to me.
I do not drink coffee, but I love Chai tea lattes which is what I ordered. Immediately, after being handed my drink I take my first sip and was thrown back at 2 things: the temperature and the flavor.
I ordered a hot chai which is always steamed, but this was luke-warm at best. The chai flavor was extremely strong and tasted very watered down like it was made with water too and not just milk. I am really not one to complain so we walked out and I tried enjoying it as much as possible, but the thought of spending the money on something and I could not even enjoy it, I felt like I had to say something.
I went back inside to let them know and she was happy to remake it for me. Since it tasted water down, I asked if they use water or milk and she said they put almond milk in it! Again, I was taken back because I never even requested almond milk and thankfully I do not have a nut allergy! (There is no description on the menu so just beware!) As far as I know, a chai latte is made with whole milk which is what I was expecting and almond milk is usually only used upon request and is an upcharge.
After she remade it, it was hotter, but still wasn't very good and I wasn't going to make an issue of it again so I let it be.  It is so unfortunate because I love the idea of having a coffee shop in the bowl, I'm just not pleased with the experience I had and don't have a desire to go back.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Kayla,
I'm very sorry to hear you didn't have a great experience at our shop! We care deeply about making every experience memorable, and it sounds like we failed to do that with your visit.  My sincerest apologies.  Regarding the chai, we do make it with whole milk as the standard, so we must have mis-heard your order to have used almond milk. I'm very sorry about that.  I'm glad we remade it for you - sorry it wasn't to your liking.  We do use a very high-quality chai that has some spice to it.  I understand that's not everyone's preference.  If there is anything else you like to drink at coffee shops, I"d love to make for you.  Ask for Madison next time you're in so we can take care of you! 

All the best,

Madison

reviews_data.review_text: GET THE BREAKFAST BURRITO. With the hot sauce side. Top notch. Good cold brew too. Would definitely come back

First time visiting this Saturday and ordered an iced Cortado. The Cortado was literally just half full and no where near the top of the cup. I also wish there were more flavor options such as different syrups. They only had two options wish is weird because what if a person doesn’t like or can’t have either option, wish was only vanilla and mocha. Not sure if I’d return.

Had a Cappuccino. While paper cup looked small it was filled to rim and tasted good.
Had an unfortunate mishap here. I went to add sugar and half&half laying on small table next to entrance door. The seating stool was placed so near to the coffee and sugar table that a teenage girl who was busy chatting with her friend with lot of hand movements and her back was facing me and sugar table.
She had no clue I was behind her adding sugar to my coffee.
I was already thinking that why this seating stool is placed so close to the sugar counter which anyone can easily strike their hand to any drinks laying on that counter. I was processing that thought and sure enough her hand struck the coffee cup, spilled on my white t-shirt and spilled on floor.
Staff was nice to replace the coffee with a new one.
Advice to the manager: please have your sugar milk counter next to water dispenser counter away from those stools where people are seating. Anyone can easily strike the drink cups accidentally if they are not aware of the counter.
Love this spot!!
Excellent lattes and amazing customer service! Please don’t change 💜
Everything from the coffee to the service is exceptional ! We love having them in our neighborhood

reviews_data.review_text: Great food options and the coffee was excellent!

Came for a breakfast burrito right when they opened and they didn’t have any. Pretty disappointing to plan my morning around going here and not get breakfast. Pretty good coffee and staff was very nice!
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Mark,
I'm very sorry we were out of brekky burritos when you arrived today. Nothing worse than looking forward to something and being let down - fully undestand that. The truth is we have been shocked by the brekky burrito demand and simply sold out faster than we expected over the weekend.  Our offsite kitchen is trying to keep up, and should be good moving forward.  We were re-loaded this afternoon, and will be slinging burritos in the morning.  If you can, please stop by so I can treat you to one - just ask for Madison. It'll be worth it, I promise. 

All the best,

Madison

reviews_data.review_text:
Grabbed a coffee before Veg Fest. The Team was absolutely crushing it. Had a line but they were calm, collected and moved through it quickly. Had the Cumulus (matcha coconut) drink iced. It was excellent. I’ll be back for a burrito.

It’s mostly outdoor seating so plan accordingly. If the weather is nice or you’re grabbing on the go this should be your spot.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Thanks so much for this kind review Garrett!  The team has been rocking it - even when things get crazy. Stoked you enjoyed your visit, and please swing back over for a burrito sometime!  Would love to say hello.

Cheers,

Madison

Fly kid Fly is fantastic. Lovely Customer service , creative drinks, tasty filter coffee. Breakfast Burritos are so good!

Great addition to the Ballantyne Community.

Come to the shop ready to have fun. Because this shop is a good time!

reviews_data.review_text: The baristas were super friendly, the coffee was great, and the aesthetic was unique! There is not much indoor seating but plenty of outdoor seating.

reviews_data.review_text:
Visited Fly Kid Fly for our first time and the inside of this coffee shop was nice and modern. The coffee shop is very small inside so there is limited seating inside so just be aware when you visit here.

The coffee wasn’t bad; however, my wife and I got our iced lattes and it was not filled up all the way which was disappointing especially for the price we paid. The coffee tasted good, but we felt like we got skimped on the serving. We understand they’re still learning so we hope it gets better soon.

We will return back, but will give it some time so they can work out their kinks.

My wife and I are excited for their Matthews location to open and hope it’s a larger coffee shop to be able to sit in and relax.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey there Andy,
I am genuinely so sorry that your drinks were not filled all the way.  I can assure you that was not intentional, but a misstep on a busy Saturday.  One of our core values as a company is to always be generous to our guests, so this is very disappointing to see.  We'd love to make it up to you next time you're in.  Please ask for Madison Currie, and I'll be sure to take care of you. 

All the best,

Madison Currie

reviews_data.review_text: Very tasty.

reviews_data.review_text: One of the best coffee shops in all of NC. Coffee is dialed, and has everything for both the average coffee drinker and the specialty coffee lover. Hospitality was next level. Thank you for having a coffee shop that actually brings your order to your table! Old school service for the win. Breakfast burritos are unreal. The vibe is so fun and has such a cool/subtle nod to flights and airplanes. Love the kid specific drink too! A must visit, family friendly, specialty coffee shop.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you!  Glad you enjoyed your experience!

reviews_data.review_text: My new favorite coffee shop. The Cloudburst was a great beverage and they nailed the Brekky Burrito. I also like that they bring your order to the table and you don't have to wait at the counter. I definitely plan to be back soon!

Got a hot mocha - very simple and flavor was as expected. Thought it was strange that no lid was given especially since this location is mostly outside seating. With it being a cooler, windy day, a lid would have helped keep coffee warmer. Food selection was average - standard pastries, nothing special.
Biggest things was the overall vibe was too modern feeling for my taste. Coffee shops should feel warm and inviting and I did not get this feeling with the aesthetics. People were friendly but overall vibe was not one where I would like to return to hang out, do a little work, etc. Wish you all well just not my preference in location.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hey Kat,
So sorry you didn't have a great experience with us! We keep our lids on the condiment station for people to add anything they need before lidding it. You should have been told where they are, so that's our fault! We do hope you come back so we can make it up to you sometime!  Just ask for Madison Currie. 

All the best! 

-Madison

reviews_data.review_text:
Fantastic new coffee shop bringing great third wave coffee to an area of Charlotte without it! It’s not often you get great third wave coffee paired with a fun, family friendly, + welcoming atmosphere.

Regular coffee bevs are top notch and the specialty drinks add a fun layer and unique twist to the coffee scene that isn’t present much in the Charlotte coffee scene. Burritos and salsa are fantastic.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for the great review Will! We are so stoked you enjoyed your time here.  Next time you're in, be sure to let us know so we can give you a high-five!

reviews_data.review_text: Many quality options to choose from, with reasonable prices. I went with the single-origin drip coffee and breakfast burrito which were solid. New go-to in the Ballantyne area.

reviews_data.review_text: I’ve been patiently waiting for this opening because Ballantyne was really lacking in coffee shop options, and it was so worth the wait. I will be back to try the breakfast burritos another time but we saw some coming out and they looked amazing too. My matcha and husband’s cold brew were both top notch. Will definitely be coming back often.

reviews_data.review_text: This is an amazing coffee shop! So glad we stopped in! Pastries were yummy and homemade, service was top notch, both the energy and vibe were great and everyone was very welcoming. Management was on point and the area around the coffee shop was so nice. We really enjoyed the outside seating, although there was great seating inside as well. There was wonderful customer service from Kara who took our order. She was very helpful, intentional and took great care of us. Deanna made the best London fog that I’ve ever had and my friend had the vanilla iced latte and said it was wonderful! I also had the matcha since the tea was so good and it was equally amazing! We decided to split the orange cinnamon roll while there and take home the cookie sandwich to my husband and son and both were delicious. They also had breakfast burritos which looked really good, so I think I’ll try that next time. This is a place I can easily say I could spend hours at. Thank you so much for the hospitality that was shown and creating such a wonderful atmosphere and serving such yummy drinks and food. Nothing went unnoticed.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Wow, thank you so much for the kind and thoughtful review! So glad you enjoyed your visit. This means a ton, and will definitely be shared with the team. Please say hi next time you’re in! 

-Madison

reviews_data.review_text: Awesome new coffee shop. Great location, good selection of pastries and breakfast burritos. Welcoming atmosphere and great customer service. Deanna recommended and made a perfect glass of iced vanilla latte! 100% recommend!
